```julia
function count_model_rows(df_cars)
    return groupby(df_cars, :model) |> g -> length(g)
end
```

This function uses the `groupby` function from the `DataFrames` package to group the data by the `:model` column. It then applies a function `g -> length(g)` which simply returns the number of rows in each group. The result is a vector containing the counts for each model.
